gomodel:SYNGO_5146  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1, 2, 3: RIL (PDLIM4) interacts with AMPA receptors (GRIA1, 2/3) and α-actinin (ACTN1 and ACTN2).\n\nFigure 3b: RIL (PDLIM4) is enriched in PSD biochemical fractions from adult rat brain as compared to homogenate and synaptosomes.\n\nFigure 3c: \"RIL immunoreactivity was concentrated in dendritic spines and showed partial colocalization with the presynaptic vesicular protein SV2 (Buckley and Kelly, 1985), confirming that in hippocampal principal neurons, RIL is localized mainly to the postsynaptic sites of synapses.\". Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Hippocampal primary cultures were prepared from embryonic day 18 Sprague Dawley tissue\"\n\n\"Generation of anti-RIL antibody. Anti-RIL polyclonal serum against the C-terminal RIL aa 317-330 peptide CDVVAVYPNAKVEL was generated at AnaSpec (San Jose, CA). Affinity purification was done by peptide-coupled SulfoLink gel (Pierce,Rockford, IL) column: 20 ml of serum, diluted 1:10 in 4°C cold PBS, was run over the column overnight at 4°C. After wash with PBS, 1 ml fractions were eluted with glycine, pH 2.5, and immediately neutralized with 1/10 volume of 1 m Tris, pH 8.0. Anti-RIL antibody (Ab)-positive fractions were selected by Western blotting of FlagRIL-expressing African green monkey kidney fibroblast cells (COS)1 lysate.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5146" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

